This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically Multiple Access Channels (MACs) with feedback and correlated channel states. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves networked systems and communication protocols, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses achievable rate regions and capacity regions, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
